headline: Norwegian Cruise Line Sails Into the Next Phase of Travel Recovery With Premium Demand in Focus
summary: Benchstone Capital exited its position in Norwegian Cruise Line during the fourth quarter as the cruise operator moves deeper into a post-reopening travel cycle. With its mix of premium and luxury brands, Norwegian is betting that higher-end demand can sustain revenue strength even as the broader travel surge normalizes.
